I don’t typically share much of what’s going on in my personal life but in this situation accountability is of the upmost importance.. 

Having been struggling with an addiction for the better part of the last couple months it was in my best interest to take a step back from all socials and quite frankly life in general to pull my head out of my ass. While I’ve dabbled on and off with substances most of my adult life while out partying and enjoying the company of friends ; never did I think I would allow something of that nature to fully engulf my life, but let me tell you what… Addiction doesn’t discriminate. And better yet you are NOT alone. It’s all too easy to get caught up in the hustle and bustle of the party scene ; especially if you’ve got a wild side like me.. 😅
Today marks one official week of sobriety. 🕺🙌 In hindsight that’s such a small amount of time but such a huge accomplishment for those who just “can’t get away” . 
Not posting this to start up some pity party, but more so to share the fact that anyone is susceptible and for those struggling with vices of their own to know even the most well rounded successful people have things going on that you may not know about so just be a nice fucking person and help others when it’s within your reach. BUT most importantly; CHECK ON YOUR FRIENDS 👏 

Addiction is giving up EVERYTHING for ONE thing, but through this journey I’ve started to learn that Recovery is giving up ONE thing for EVERYTHING.. 🔨 

Brb, getting back to ME… 🕺 👏
